{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Root cause: commit 703661409 (compliable-stretchy-bee) added the no-commit-to-branch pre-commit hook (args --branch main --branch master). CI's 'lint + type-check' job runs 'pre-commit run --all-files' while checked out on main (post-merge branch CI), so the hook fires and fails the whole job on every main push. The only green run (29464899221) was on a feature branch (test/fd84-guardfire), where HEAD != main so the hook passes. The Gerrit Verified mirror checks out at refs/changes/* (detached HEAD) so it passes today.\n\nFix: add 'env: SKIP: no-commit-to-branch' to the pre-commit step in .github/workflows/test.yml AND .github/workflows/gerrit-verify.yaml. The hook stays in .pre-commit-config.yaml as the local commit-time guardrail; the real land-through-Gerrit enforcement is server-side (GitHub ruleset + two Gerrit votes).\n\nVerified locally: on a branch named 'master' the hook reports Failed/exit1 (reproduces CI); with SKIP set it reports Skipped/exit0. Full 'SKIP=no-commit-to-branch pre-commit run --all-files' passes (check-yaml/toml/merge-conflict/large-files + make lint + make typecheck all green); make config-check green.\n\nNote (separate pre-existing issue, NOT fixed here): the pytest job also shows a FLAKY 'fatal: could not parse HEAD' git race (known bug edf7) hitting different tests across runs (test_guard_counts_only_direct_children_not_unrelated, test_benchmark_commit_count_is_ceil_per_pass). That is an intermittent store-write race with existing mitigation code, tracked separately from this deterministic lint regression."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784227335503601001,"uuid":"57d0af6e-7e9a-4620-b310-027419b1fbc2"}